libifp
------------------------------------------
libifp is a general-purpose library-driver for iRiver iFP (flash-based)
portable audio players. The source code is pure C and is fairly portable.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.4.1-1
  libiconv2-1.14-3
  libifp-devel-1.0.0.2-1bl2
  libifp4-1.0.0.2-1bl2
  libusb0-1.2.6.0-2
  pkg-config-0.29-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.25-4
  cygport-0.21.1-1
  gcc-core-5.3.0-3
  libtool-2.4.6-3
  make-4.1-1

Canonical website:
  http://ifp-driver.sf.net/

Canonical download:
  mirror://sourceforge/ifp-driver/libifp-1.0.0.2.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libifp-1.0.0.2-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libifp-1.0.0.2-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libifp-1.0.0.2-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libifp-1.0.0.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libifp4-1.0.0.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libifp-devel-1.0.0.2-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libifp)
  /usr/bin/ifp_simple.exe
  /usr/bin/ifpline.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libifp.README
  /usr/share/doc/libifp/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/libifp/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/libifp/README
  /usr/share/doc/libifp/TODO

(libifp4)
  /usr/bin/cygifp-4.dll

(libifp-devel)
  /usr/include/ifp.h
  /usr/lib/libifp.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libifp.pc
  /usr/share/man/man3/ifp.h.3.gz

------------------

